

sSMTP Configuration

1.Install ssmtp:
    sudo apt-get install ssmtp

2.Make changes in ssmtp.conf file:

    gksu gedit /etc/ssmtp/ssmtp.conf

    root = Your Email Address

    mailhub = smtp.cse.iitb.ac.in

    rewriteDomain = cse.iitb.ac.in

    AuthUser = Your Email Address

    AuthPass = Your Password

    fromLineOverride = YES

    UseTLS = YES

    UseSTARTTLS = YES

3.Write into file /etc/ssmtp/revaliases

    root: Your Email:mail.cse.iitb.ac.in:25

4.Give your email address in /usr/local/nagios/etc/objects/contacts.cfg

